FizzBuzz
========

Practice confronting your roommate with an AI designed to be the most annoying, elusive,
distracting, and unyielding roommate ever.

Run
---

```bash
npm install
npm run dev
```

Open the URL printed by the dev server. It starts at `http://127.0.0.1:5175`, but if that
port is already busy it will try the next port.

Project setup
-------------

FizzBuzz is now an Express + Vite app:

- `server/index.js` - Express API server, `.env` loading, Gemini image-generation hook.
- `client/index.html` - Vite HTML entry.
- `client/src/main.js` - frontend interaction logic.
- `client/src/styles.css` - game UI styling.
- `vite.config.js` - Vite build config, outputting production assets to `dist/client`.

`npm run dev` runs the Express backend and mounts Vite as dev middleware, so the frontend
and `/api/*` routes share the same origin.

API routes
----------

- `GET /api/health` - service status and integration flags.
- `POST /api/session` - creates a confrontation session from `argument`, `evidence`, and `aggro`.
- `POST /api/argue` - advances the boss battle for a `sessionId`, optionally using a live `transcript`.
- `POST /api/media/forehead` - turns an uploaded face into a wide-angle forehead boss portrait.
- `POST /api/voice/token` - mints a temporary Deepgram token for browser live transcription.
- `POST /api/media/avatar` - placeholder for Pika avatar/video generation.

Copy `.env.example` to `.env` when adding real keys.

Forehead mode uses Google's Nano Banana image API. It stays in mock mode until both of these
are set:

```bash
GEMINI_API_KEY=your_key_here
USE_GEMINI_IMAGE=true
```

Voice mode uses Deepgram live transcription. The browser asks the backend for a short-lived
token, opens a Deepgram Listen WebSocket, and streams mic audio while the transcript updates
in the boss battle. It falls back to browser speech captions when Deepgram is off.

```bash
DEEPGRAM_API_KEY=your_key_here
USE_DEEPGRAM=true
```
